      className="float"
      aspectRatio="inherit"
      style={{ marginLeft: "1em" }}
    />

    <p>
      Spencer Chang is an artist, engineer, and toymaker interested in the play,
      creation, and care that emerges from our relationships with and through
      technology.
    </p>
    <p>
      They make <a
        href="https://www.are.na/spencer-chang/communal-computing-infrastructure"
        >communal computing infrastructure</a
      >—playful, intimate, and empowering forms of technology made to be used
      and loved by people. These include:
    </p>
    <ol class="list-decimal list-inside pl-8">
      <!-- TODO: add floating image hover preview for each of these, support for hosted creations to show their preview -->
      <li>
        <i><b style="font-weight: 600">infrastructure</b></i> (
        <span class="">
          <a href="/creation/playhtml">creative tools</a>,
          <a href="/creation/touching-computers-creating-data-talismans"
            >experimental interfaces</a
          >,
          <a href="/creation/gather">local-first apps</a>,
          <a href="/creation/verses-verses">text playgrounds</a>,
          <a href="/creation/i-love-living">archival automations</a>,
          <a href="/creation/syllabus-taking-an-internet-walk"
            >instruction manuals</a
          >
        </span>)
      </li>
      <li class="mt-2">
        <i><b style="font-weight: 600">environments</b></i> (
        <span class="">
          <a href="/creation/html-garden">living ecosystems</a>,
          <a href="/creation/poems-we-found-with-the-internet">playful spaces</a
          >,
          <a href="/creation/everyday">phone interventions</a>,
          <a href="/creation/cursor-watching">live windows</a>,
          <a href="/creation/neighborhood-internets-workshop"
            >creating neighborhood internets</a
          >,
          <a href="/creation/(we)bsite">collections of dreams</a>,
          <a href="/creation/8-bite">games</a>
        </span>)
      </li>
    </ol>

    <p>
      Their practice—spanning internet spaces, interactive sculpture, and
      creative infrastructure—transforms technology from a tool for
      institutional control into one for collective well-being. These works
      leverage whimsical intimacy to interrogate our systems, invite active
      imagination to reinvent them, and finally, equip us with the means to do
      so. Combining design and art into “useful art”, their tools, games, and
      spaces question what websites are, who we can be through the internet, and
      how technology might become a public good.
    </p>

    <p>
      Chang's work has been showcased and supported internationally, including
      Hyundai Artlab (Seoul), Tokyo Geidai (Tokyo), Gray Area (San Francisco),
      CultureHub (New York), WSA (New York), the Museum of Moving Image (New
      York), Alserkal Avenue (Dubai), and the de Young Museum (San Francisco).
      Their projects have been featured in MIT Technology Review, It's Nice
      That, and Frieze, and supported through grants by the San Francisco Arts
      Commission, APOSSIBLE, and the Ethereum Foundation. A NEW INC (New Museum)
      Y11 member, they have taught and led workshops for institutions such as
      the School for Poetic Computation, Stanford University, and the Asian Art
      Museum, among others around the world.
    </p>

